<h1>Problem 642 - 2011 USA TST, P6 of 9</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>A polynomial \(P(x)\) is called nice if \(P(0) = 1\) and the nonzero coefficients of \(P(x)\) alternate between \(1\) and \(-1\) when written in order. Suppose that \(P(x)\) is nice, and let \(m\) and \(n\) be two relatively prime positive integers. Show that \[Q(x) = P(x^n) \cdot \frac{(x^{mn} - 1)(x-1)}{(x^m-1)(x^n-1)}\] is nice as well.</p>
